This paper discusses the release of the 2016 edition of Google Scholar Metrics, which is related to the field of information retrieval (cs.IR) and data mining (cs.DL). The addition and elimination of language rankings may also involve natural language processing (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CR) in terms of language security. The mention of working paper and discussion paper series may also relate to cybernetics (cs.CY) in terms of communication and dissemination of research.
